# Solution: rust_web_social_expert_073_architectural_understanding_expert_01

## Executive Summary

This architectural analysis examines the EduPulse Live platform, an event-driven social learning system built in Rust. The platform follows a CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) architecture with an event-sourcing pattern. After thorough analysis of the codebase, I have identified the core architectural components, traced a complete data flow, and developed a strategic integration plan for the proposed Real-time Collaborative Whiteboard feature.

---

## Key Files Identified

### Configuration and Infrastructure
- `/app/project/src/config.txt` - Application configuration with database, broker, auth, and search settings
- `/app/project/package.json` - Frontend dependencies including socket.io-client for real-time communications

### Authentication & Session Management
- `/app/project/src/module_1.txt` - **AuthenticationService** - JWT-based authentication with Redis session management, bcrypt password hashing, and role-based access control

### Event Bus Infrastructure
- `/app/project/src/module_4.txt` - **EventPublisher & EventStore** - Core event infrastructure using NATS JetStream with event sourcing
- `/app/project/src/module_9.txt` - **Outbox Pattern Implementation** - Reliable event publishing with Ed25519 signatures and NATS broker
- `/app/project/src/module_12.txt` - **Event Bus Abstraction** - NATS-backed event bus with in-process fan-out and back-pressure awareness
- `/app/project/src/module_50.txt` - **Outbox Processor** - RabbitMQ/AMQP event publishing with exponential backoff retries

### Domain Services (Write Model)
- `/app/project/src/module_33.txt` - **PulseService** - Learning Pulse domain with Service/Repository/EventPublisher pattern
- `/app/project/src/module_60.txt` - **PulseService (Alternative)** - Business logic for creating learning pulses and handling student replies
- `/app/project/src/module_81.txt` - **LearningPulseService** - Domain model with validation, event generation, and persistence

### Event Consumers (Read Model / CQRS Projections)
- `/app/project/src/module_15.txt` - **Badge Awarding Service** - Event consumer that awards badges based on domain events
- `/app/project/src/module_27.txt` - **Search Indexing Service** - Event consumer that indexes pulses into Elasticsearch
- `/app/project/src/module_20.txt` - **EventDispatcher** - Combines event store persistence with in-process fan-out

### Event Infrastructure (Multiple Broker Support)
- `/app/project/src/module_64.txt` - **Kafka EventBus** - Kafka-backed event bus with audit trail consumer
- `/app/project/src/module_72.txt` - **NATS EventPublisher** - Domain event infrastructure with typed events and NATS publishing

### GDPR & Compliance
- `/app/project/src/module_45.txt` - **GDPR Erasure Service** - Event-sourced user data erasure with soft-delete events
- `/app/project/src/module_6.txt` - **Audit Event Store** - GDPR-compliant event store with pseudonymization support

---

## Code Evidence

### 1. Authentication & Session Management (module_1.txt)

