//! src/module_15.rs
//!
//! Badge-Awarding Worker
//! ---------------------
//! This module implements a background worker that listens to domain events and
//! awards badges to users when they satisfy certain achievement criteria.  It
//! showcases:
//!  • Event-driven, fully asynchronous architecture
//!  • Clean separation of Event-handling / Repository / Service concerns
//!  • Structured logging via `tracing`
//!  • Strong typing for event payloads
//!
//! In production this worker would be deployed as a separate binary or k8s job,
//! connected to the message broker (NATS / RabbitMQ / Kafka).  For testability
//! the broker abstraction is hidden behind an `EventConsumer` trait.
